<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-29T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-29T19:00:00-05:00" n="63" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d63">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">884.24/9–2944: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-29T20:00:00-04:00">September 29, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>141. Military equipment including 5,000 rifles, 5 armored cars,
                                twelve 37mm. field guns, four 75mm. field guns, fifty 30 cal.
                                Browning <pb facs="0087" n="75" xml:id="pg_75"/> machine guns, fifty
                                45 cal. submachine guns and ammunition has been assigned to Ethiopia
                                and will probably be shipped within a month. Date of shipment will
                                be announced to you as soon as known.</p>
                            <p>Please inform Ethiopian Government.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>